  "text": "We denote with p the LMS filter order and with μ its step size. The step size μ is upper bounded by 2/λ max , where λ max is the maximum eigenvalue of the auto-correlation matrix R = E[XX H ], where X H is the Hermitian transpose, or conjugate transpose, of X. Observe that if μ is chosen too small, the time to converge to optimal weights tends to be large [CITATION_1] . The adversary initializes the weight matrix W to be equal to the zero matrix. Then, the adversary's algorithm shown in Algorithm 1, is run online. It is worth noting that in this algorithm; X is the input signal, e is the error,ē is its complex conjugate, and d is the desired output signal.",
